All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ant
    The Ant class represents ants that are created and used during a stochastic simulation execution.
    AntColony
    The AntColony class that represents a colony of Ants and is a subclass of the Colony abstract class.
    Colony<T>
    Abstract class for colonies of generic elements T.
    DeterministicEvent
    DeterministicEvent is an abstract class that implements the interface IEvent.
    Edge
    Class Edge represents an edge of the weighted graph, belonging to the WGraph class.
    Evaporation
    The Evaporation class is a subclass of the abstract class StochasticEvent, from which it inherits the field time and the simulation.
    EventComparator
    EventComparator class implements the interface Comparator provided by java.util library.
    GenericGraph<T>
    Abstract class for the graph with generic nodes T.
    Graph
    Graph class is a subclass of the abstract class GenericGraph by parameterizing the generic node T as a type Node class.
    HamiltonianSimulation
    HamiltonianSimulation is a subclass of the Simulation class.
    IEvent
    Interface for Events.
    ISimulation
    Interface for the Simulation.
    Main
    Main class contains only the method main which parses the xml file received as argument and runs the Hamiltonian stochastic simulation.
    Move
    The Move class is a subclass of the abstract class StochasticEvent, from which it inherits the field time and the simulation.
    Multinomial
    Class Multinomial defines a multinomial distribution and a method to sample from it.
    Node
    Class Node represents a node of the graph.
    Parser
    Parser class is a subclass of the DefaultHandler abstract class provided by the org.xml.sax.helpers library.
    PEC
    Implementation of the PECInterface where the PEC is implemented as a priority queue of interface event objects.
    PECInterface
    Interface for the PEC (Pending event container).
    ShowResults
    The ShowResults class is a subclass of the abstract class DeterministicEvent, from which it inherits the field time, and the hamiltonian simulation.
    Simulation
    Abstract class that implements the interface ISimulation.
    StochasticEvent
    Abstract class StochasticEvent implements the interface IEvent.
    Utils
    Class Utils implements the method expRandom.
    WGraph
    Weighted Graph class is a subclass of Graph where the weights of the edges are used to define the shortest path of a graph and its corresponding weight.
